#Text=AT AN UPPER WINDOW
#Text=It was very early the next morning -- a time of sun and dew .

#Text=The confused beginnings of many birds ' songs spread into the healthy air , and the wan blue of the heaven was here and there coated with thin webs of incorporeal cloud which were of no effect in obscuring day .
#Text=All the lights in the scene were yellow as to colour , and all the shadows were attenuated as to form .
#Text=The creeping plants about the old manor-house were bowed with rows of heavy water drops , which had upon objects behind them the effect of minute lenses of high magnifying power .
#Text=Just before the clock struck five Gabriel Oak and Coggan passed the village cross , and went on together to the fields .
#Text=They were yet barely in view of their mistress 's house , when Oak fancied he saw the opening of a casement in one of the upper windows .
#Text=The two men were at this moment partially screened by an elder bush , now beginning to be enriched with black bunches of fruit , and they paused before emerging from its shade .
#Text=A handsome man leaned idly from the lattice .
#Text=He looked east and then west , in the manner of one who makes a first morning survey .
#Text=The man was Sergeant Troy .
#Text=His red jacket was loosely thrown on , but not buttoned , and he had altogether the relaxed bearing of a soldier taking his ease .
#Text=Coggan spoke first , looking quietly at the window .
#Text=" She has married him ! " he said .
#Text=Gabriel had previously beheld the sight , and he now stood with his back turned , making no reply .
#Text=" I fancied we should know something to-day , " continued Coggan .
#Text=" I heard wheels pass my door just after dark -- you were out somewhere . "
#Text=He glanced round upon Gabriel .
#Text=" Good heavens above us , Oak , how white your face is ; you look like a corpse ! "
#Text=" Do I ? " said Oak , with a faint smile .
#Text=" Lean on the gate : I 'll wait a bit . "
#Text=" All right , all right . "
#Text=They stood by the gate awhile , Gabriel listlessly staring at the ground .
#Text=His mind sped into the future , and saw there enacted in years of leisure the scenes of repentance that would ensue from this work of haste .
#Text=That they were married he had instantly decided .
#Text=Why had it been so mysteriously managed ?
#Text=It had become known that she had had a fearful journey to Bath , owing to her miscalculating the distance :
#Text=that the horse had broken down , and that she had been more than two days getting there .
#Text=It was not Bathsheba 's way to do things furtively .
#Text=With all her faults , she was candour itself .
#Text=Could she have been entrapped ?
#Text=The union was not only an unutterable grief to him :
#Text=it amazed him , notwithstanding that he had passed the preceding week in a suspicion that such might be the issue of Troy 's meeting her away from home .
#Text=Her quiet return with Liddy had to some extent dispersed the dread .

#Text=Just as that imperceptible motion which appears like stillness is infinitely divided in its properties from stillness itself , so had his hope undistinguishable from despair differed from despair indeed .
#Text=In a few minutes they moved on again towards the house .
#Text=The sergeant still looked from the window .
#Text=" Morning , comrades ! " he shouted , in a cheery voice , when they came up .
#Text=Coggan replied to the greeting .
#Text=" Bai n't ye going to answer the man ? " he then said to Gabriel .
#Text=" I 'd say good morning -- you need n't spend a hapenny of meaning upon it , and yet keep the man civil . "
#Text=Gabriel soon decided too that , since the deed was done , to put the best face upon the matter would be the greatest kindness to her he loved .
#Text=" Good morning , Sergeant Troy , " he returned , in a ghastly voice .
#Text=" A rambling , gloomy house this , " said Troy , smiling .
#Text=" Why -- they MAY not be married ! " suggested Coggan .
#Text=" Perhaps she 's not there . "
#Text=Gabriel shook his head .
#Text=The soldier turned a little towards the east , and the sun kindled his scarlet coat to an orange glow .
#Text=" But it is a nice old house , " responded Gabriel .
#Text=" Yes -- I suppose so ; but I feel like new wine in an old bottle here .

column1: #Text=" do you know if insanity has ever appeared in Mr. Boldwood 's family ? "
#Text=Jan reflected for a moment .
#Text=" I once heard that an uncle of his was queer in his head , but I do n't know the rights o't , " he said .
#Text=" It is of no importance , " said Troy , lightly .
#Text=" Well , I shall be down in the fields with you some time this week ; but I have a few matters to attend to first .
